Detailed Description

StatusProvider is the provider to retrieve states about the mobile station. An instance of this class is part of the Apoxi Data Control. A pointer to this provider can be retrieved from the main provider via the id:

c_status_provider_id

Following column ids are defined: c_mode_id :NumberType: cast to RegisterMode c_state_id :NumberType: cast to RegisterStatus c_reject_cause_id :NumberType: cast to RegisterRejectCause c_mcc_id :NumberType: cast to Mcc c_mnc_id :NumberType: cast to Mnc c_mnc_threedigits_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN, tells if MNC has three digits. c_signal_strength_id :NumberType: cast to SignalStrengthLevel c_signal_quality_id :NumberType: cast to SignalQualityLevel c_signal_strength_max_id:NumberType: cast to SignalStrengthMax c_signal_quality_max_id :NumberType: cast to SignalQualityMax c_battery_load_id :NumberType: cast to BatteryLoadLevel c_clir_mode_id :NumberType: cast to ClirMode c_redialing_active_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_network_name_long_id :WStringType: c_network_name_short_id :WStringType: c_gprs_available_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_gprs_attached_id :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_tz_offset_id :NumberType: c_tz_dst_id :NumberType: c_succ_16bit_conc_sms_ref_no :NumberType: c_last_ccm_id :NumberType: cast to UINT32 (last current call meter line 1) c_last_ccm2_id :NumberType: cast to UINT32 (last current call meter line 2) c_lai_mcc_id :NumberType: cast to Mcc c_lai_mnc_id :NumberType: cast to Mnc c_lai_lac_id :NumberType: c_eep_calibration_status_id :NumberType: c_cellid_id :NumberType: cast to UINT32

This provider only consists of one fixed row.

NOTE: Please do not instantiate this class.
